- Beatles For Sale is an early studio album from the Beatles (1964) and reflects their mid‑1960s, road‑worn sound; it includes several cover songs and a generally more subdued, autumnal mood compared with their later innovative work. As a standalone early album it has historical importance and moments of strong songwriting, but it is more of a period piece with a relatively uniform sonic character and several non-original tracks. For a CD listener seeking a broad, immediately gratifying experience of an artist’s highlights, this particular Beatles album is less of an obvious single-disc “best of” choice than a compilation would be.
